🎥 Project Demo Video Planning
Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System

This plan helps you create a clear, professional demo video that explains the system end-to-end for stakeholders, interviews, or product presentation.

1. Objective of the Demo Video

The video should demonstrate:

How onboarding is automated
How offboarding is securely handled
How roles (HR, IT, Manager, Employee) interact
How workflows, access control, and data integrity work together
Business value (speed, security, automation)
2. Target Audience
HR Teams
IT/Admin Teams
Security/Compliance Teams
Technical Interview Panel
Investors / Stakeholders
3. Video Structure (Recommended Flow)
Intro → Problem → Solution → System Demo → Architecture → Workflow → Benefits → Conclusion
4. Scene-by-Scene Breakdown
🎬 Scene 1: Introduction (0:00 – 0:20)

Visual:

Title screen: “Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System”

Narration:

Problem of manual HR onboarding/offboarding
Delays, errors, security risks
🎬 Scene 2: Problem Statement (0:20 – 0:50)

Visual:

HR paperwork, delayed approvals, IT tickets

Narration:

Manual onboarding takes days
Access provisioning errors
Security risks during employee exit
🎬 Scene 3: Solution Overview (0:50 – 1:20)

Visual:

System dashboard animation

Narration:

Fully automated workflow-based system
HR → IT → IAM → Employee lifecycle automation
🎬 Scene 4: System Demo (Core Section) (1:20 – 3:30)
👤 Onboarding Demo Flow
HR creates employee
→ System triggers workflow
→ IT auto-provisions access
→ Manager approval
→ Employee gets onboarding checklist
→ Status = ACTIVE
🧪 Show UI Screens:
Employee creation form
Workflow status tracker
Access provisioning screen
Employee dashboard
🚪 Offboarding Demo Flow
Exit request initiated
→ Manager approval
→ IT revokes access
→ IAM sync disables accounts
→ Data archived
→ Status = EXITED
🎬 Scene 5: Architecture Explanation (3:30 – 4:30)

Visual:

UI → API Gateway → Workflow Engine → Services → Database + IAM + Audit Logs

Narration:

Microservices or layered architecture
Event-driven automation
Secure data flow
🎬 Scene 6: Automation & Rules (4:30 – 5:30)

Visual:

Rule engine animation
Event triggers (NEW_HIRE, EXIT_APPROVED)

Narration:

Business rules control lifecycle
Automated decision-making
No manual intervention required
🎬 Scene 7: Security & Access Control (5:30 – 6:00)

Visual:

Lock icons, RBAC diagram

Narration:

Role-based access control
Least privilege enforcement
Secure offboarding ensures zero leftover access
🎬 Scene 8: Benefits (6:00 – 6:40)

Show Impact:

⏱ Faster onboarding (hours instead of days)
🔐 Improved security
📉 Reduced manual HR workload
📊 Full audit tracking
⚙️ Scalable automation
🎬 Scene 9: Conclusion (6:40 – 7:00)

Visual:

System dashboard summary

Narration:

End-to-end automated employee lifecycle system
Reliable, scalable, and secure
5. Visual Assets Checklist

You will need:

Dashboard UI screens
Workflow diagrams
Architecture diagram
Role-based UI views
Animation of onboarding/offboarding flow
Icons (HR, IT, Security, Employee)
